        <definition>Key erbsland::cterm::Input::readKey</definition>
        <argsstring>(std::chrono::milliseconds timeout={}) const</argsstring>
        <name>readKey</name>
        <qualifiedname>erbsland::cterm::Input::readKey</qualifiedname>
        <param>
          <type>std::chrono::milliseconds</type>
          <declname>timeout</declname>
          <defval>{}</defval>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Read one key event without blocking longer than the given timeout. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>In <computeroutput><ref refid="classerbsland_1_1cterm_1_1_input_1ac97391a4c58205cba04e026ee29a4816a897356954c2cd3d41b221e3f24f99bba" kindref="member">Mode::Key</ref></computeroutput>, any timeout less than or equal to zero is normalized to zero and performs a non-blocking poll. In <computeroutput><ref refid="classerbsland_1_1cterm_1_1_input_1ac97391a4c58205cba04e026ee29a4816a299040a8206f805f0a777fc25b6df6a9" kindref="member">Mode::ReadLine</ref></computeroutput>, the timeout is ignored and this call behaves like a blocking line read converted into <computeroutput><ref refid="classerbsland_1_1cterm_1_1_key" kindref="compound">Key</ref></computeroutput>. <parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>timeout</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Maximum wait time in <computeroutput><ref refid="classerbsland_1_1cterm_1_1_input_1ac97391a4c58205cba04e026ee29a4816a897356954c2cd3d41b221e3f24f99bba" kindref="member">Mode::Key</ref></computeroutput>. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>The parsed key event, or an invalid key if no supported input was read before the timeout expired. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="erbsland/cterm/Input.hpp" line="44" column="10" bodyfile="erbsland/cterm/Input.hpp" bodystart="44" bodyend="49"/>
      </memberdef>
